                      mark the midpoint of the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</ref>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id="a18">
                    <locus target="#84v" facs="171">Fol. 84v</locus>
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">Note of secondary ownership, Särṣä Maryam, his brother Ṣǝge Dǝngǝl, etc. ;Sege</desc>
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id="a19">
                      <locus target="#166r" facs="334"> f. 166r, col. 1, top</locus>
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">Note of ownership by Ḫǝsqǝyas and his son, Qalä Wäld</desc>
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                      <locus target="#167v" facs="337">Fol. 167v</locus>
                      <desc>illegible text and pen trails</desc>
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                      <locus target="#ii #28 #58 #78 #98 #120 #146 #160" facs="004 058 118 158 198 244 294 322">Fols. ii, 28, 58, 78, 98, 120, 146, 160</locus>
                      <desc>purple yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark the location of illuminations as navigation system</desc>
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                      <locus target="#115" facs="232">Fol. 115</locus>
                      <desc>red yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark content as navigation system</desc>
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                      <locus target="#18v #19v #33v #34r #40v" facs="039 041 069 070 083">Fols. 18v, 19v, 33v, 34r, 40v</locus>
                      <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearl</desc>
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                      <locus target="#26v #40r #77r #102v #119r" facs="055 082 156 207 240">Fols. 26v, 40r, 77r, 102v, 119r</locus>
                      <desc>etc., lines of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#22r #24r #28r #35r #38r" facs="046 050 058 072 078">Fols. 22r, 24r, 28r, 35r, 38r</locus>
                      <desc>etc., text has been removed</desc>
                      </item>
                    <item xml:id="e9">
                      <locus target="#13r" facs="028">Fol. 13r</locus>
                      <desc>The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text
                        above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line</desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                <bindingDesc>
                  <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="partly">
                    <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards (repaired).</decoNote>
                    <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                      <material key="parchment"/>
                      <material key="wood"/>
                    </decoNote>
                  </binding>
                </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
